219":"1219","30 July 1243":"30 July 1243","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland","Acre, Palestine":"Acre, Northern, Palestine","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Torun","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Galician (<b>Torán</b>): habitational name from the village of Santa María de Torán in Ourense province, Galicia (Spain).","Irish: variant of   Torrens  . This form of the surname is very rare in Britain and Ireland, and is found mainly in Lancashire, England."],"variants":[{"name":"Torrens","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Raul, Jaime, Jorge, Luis, Manuel, Aida, Alejandro, Ana, Andres, Anselmo, Benito, Caridad.","Catalan: altered form of <b>Torrents</b>, a topographic name for someone living by the course of a torrent, from the plural of Catalan <i>torrent</i> ‘mountain stream, torrent’ (from Latin <i>torrens</i>).","Irish (Derry and Antrim): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Toráin</b>, <b>Ó Taráin</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Torán</i>’, a personal name formed from a diminutive of Gaelic <i>tor</i> ‘tower, champion, hero’, or possibly a borrowing of Norse <i>Thorfinn</i>, compare   Corrin  . The final extraneous or possessive <i>-s</i> (sometimes spelt <i>-ce</i>) is not original."]}]},{"name":"Stefanos","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Stephen</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephen","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Stefanos Torun was born on 1 January 1224, in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland, his father, Sir Wradislauw Torun, was 47 and his mother, Krystyne Slavik, was 24. He married Guarda Saxon in 1275, in T